.TH YEET 1 "July 2026" "Yeet 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
yeet \- native drag-and-drop shelf for Wayland and Windows
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B yeet
.RI [ OPTION ]... [ FILE ]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Yeet holds files and snippets temporarily so they can be dragged into another
application later. Running the command again forwards arguments to the existing
desktop-session instance.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-toggle
Show or hide the shelf.
.TP
.B \-\-clear
Remove all unpinned items.
.TP
.B \-\-hidden
Start the primary instance without showing its shelf.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Show command-line help.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show the installed version.
.SH SHORTCUTS
.TP
.B Ctrl+A
Select every shelf item.
.TP
.B Delete
Remove selected items.
.TP
.B Space
Preview the first selected item.
.TP
.B Escape
Hide the shelf.
.SH WAYLAND
On compositors supporting layer-shell, Yeet creates a drop target at the right
edge of each monitor. On GNOME and compositors without layer-shell, bind
.B yeet --toggle
in the desktop shortcut settings.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/yeet/settings.json
Per-user preferences.
.TP
.I $XDG_DATA_HOME/yeet/shelf.json
Persisted shelf state.
.SH SEE ALSO
Project documentation: https://github.com/hjosugi/wayland-yeet
